drm: cix: demote missing DPTX dp_phy fallback log

Some DPTX instances do not expose an external dp_phy reference, but
the driver continues by registering its built-in USB-DP/eDP PHY helpers.
Report that valid fallback at debug level so normal boots do not show
a warning for working display blocks.

--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/cix/dptx/trilin_dptx.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/cix/dptx/trilin_dptx.c
@@ -2341,7 +2341,7 @@
 		}
 
 		if (IS_ERR_OR_NULL(phy->base))
-			DP_WARN("no dp_phy\n");
+			DP_DEBUG("no dp_phy, using built-in DPTX PHY registration\n");
 
 		trilin_usbdp_phy_register(dp);
 		trilin_edp_phy_register(dp);
